    },
    {
      "id": "1a76adc5_b88803c6",
      "file_path": "tpm-util/import/main.c",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 185,
      "message": "It is part of the input from the kube node admin. If no password is provided, access to primarykey is not secure. I am not sure if we should make this optional.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 301,
        "name": "Kiran Kamineni",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "kiran.k.kamineni@intel.com",
        "username": "kirankamineni"
      },
      "updated": "2018-09-01 00:33:57.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "1a76adc5_58abef74",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "1a76adc5_74f02f91",
      "file_path": "tpm-util/import/main.c",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 185,
      "message": "Ok. The reason I am suggesting is that import utility is a tool/wrapper around the Tss2_Sys_Import call. TPM has support with and without key password. May be in future there may be a requirement like that and this tool shouldn't limit it.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 285,
        "name": "Ritu Sood",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "ritu.sood@intel.com",
        "username": "ritusood"
      },
      "updated": "2018-09-04 16:59:35.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "1a76adc5_b88803c6",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "1a76adc5_548173c2",
      "file_path": "tpm-util/import/main.c",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 185,
      "message": "Ok, I will update the tool itself to maintain that optional nature from the underlying call. We can enforce the password from a deployment configuration if needed.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 301,
        "name": "Kiran Kamineni",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "kiran.k.kamineni@intel.com",
        "username": "kirankamineni"
      },
      "updated": "2018-09-04 17:18:31.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "1a76adc5_74f02f91",
      "unresolved": false
    },
